<p><a name="Further_reading" id="Further_reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Espresso&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFIllyIlly.2C_Ricardo1989.2F1992">Illy, Francesco; Illy, Ricardo (1989/1992). <i>The Book of Coffee</i>. Milano: Abbeville Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1558593217" class="internal">ISBN 1558593217</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Book+of+Coffee&amp;rft.aulast=Illy&amp;rft.aufirst=Francesco&amp;rft.au=Illy%2C+Francesco&amp;rft.au=Illy%2C+Ricardo&amp;rft.date=1989%2F1992&amp;rft.place=Milano&amp;rft.pub=Abbeville+Press&amp;rft.isbn=1558593217&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Espresso"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFIllyViani.2C_Rinantonio">Illy, Andrea; Viani, Rinantonio. <i>Espresso: The Science of Quality</i>. Academic Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0123703719" class="internal">ISBN 0123703719</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Espresso%3A+The+Science+of+Quality&amp;rft.aulast=Illy&amp;rft.aufirst=Andrea&amp;rft.au=Illy%2C+Andrea&amp;rft.au=Viani%2C+Rinantonio&amp;rft.pub=Academic+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0123703719&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Espresso"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFBersten1993">Bersten, Ian (1993). <i>Coffee Floats Tea Sinks: Through History and Technology to a Complete Understanding</i>. Helian Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0646091808" class="internal">ISBN 0646091808</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Coffee+Floats+Tea+Sinks%3A+Through+History+and+Technology+to+a+Complete+Understanding&amp;rft.aulast=Bersten&amp;rft.aufirst=Ian&amp;rft.au=Bersten%2C+Ian&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.pub=Helian+Books&amp;rft.isbn=0646091808&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Espresso"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFFumagalli1995">Fumagalli, Ambrogio (1995). <i>Coffee Makers</i>. Chronicle Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0811810828" class="internal">ISBN 0811810828</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Coffee+Makers&amp;rft.aulast=Fumagalli&amp;rft.aufirst=Ambrogio&amp;rft.au=Fumagalli%2C+Ambrogio&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.pub=Chronicle+Books&amp;rft.isbn=0811810828&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Espresso"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cs.usyd.edu.au/~bob/Coffee/timeline.html" class="external text" title="http://www.cs.usyd.edu.au/~bob/Coffee/timeline.html" rel="nofollow">An espresso timeline</a>, with illustrations.</li>
<li>Adam Dean, <i><a href="http://www.wholelattelove.com/articles/founding_fathers_of_espresso.cfm" class="external text" title="http://www.wholelattelove.com/articles/founding_fathers_of_espresso.cfm" rel="nofollow">The Founding Fathers of Espresso</a></i>, www.wholelattelove.com. Mainly an online summary of Bersten's original research (see above) on the development of the espresso machine by <a href="/w/index.php?title=Luigi_Bezzera&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Luigi Bezzera (page does not exist)">Luigi Bezzera</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Desiderio_Pavoni&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Desiderio Pavoni (page does not exist)">Desiderio Pavoni</a> and <a href="/w/index.php?title=Giovanni_Achille_Gaggia&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Giovanni Achille Gaggia (page does not exist)">Giovanni Achille Gaggia</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.jlhufford.com/articles/espressogreek.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.jlhufford.com/articles/espressogreek.asp" rel="nofollow">Espresso, an Ancient Greek Perspective</a>, by James Pappas</li>
</ul>
